deck: The only knight of old to have been born and live in Flatbush.
description:
Origin

Sir Butch was a young (teenage?) tough guy from Brooklyn wearing a Dink or Rat Cap (like Jughead) who spoke in dems and does who spent his time hanging out in Flatbush stealing apples, playing stick ball in the street despite traffic and bothering the local cops.

One day while on the run form officer Clancy he falls through an open manhole and finds himself transported to a time of knights in shining armor, while there he defeats an evil wizard named Floda Reltin (Adolf `nitler’ backwards) and is made a Knight of the Square Table before being returned to Brooklyn by a friendly wizard.

After that Butch finds himself stumbling into other portals and returning to the kingdom that knows him as Sir Butch where he battles a series of giants, wizards, evil knights, and one time even Loki the God of Mischief, he also from time to time brings back magic items from the Kingdom which he uses to prank the cops on patrol on his street in Flatbush.

Sir Butch was an early creation of Dave Berg of Mad Magazine fame, the character never had a regular home comic but seemed to be moved from one too another as filler as needed.

This Fawcett Sir Butch is not to be confused with the sometimes sidekick of the Shining Knight also known as Sir Butch over at DC.
name: Sir Butch

Cascade's own powers let her escape however, where her mother could not. She gathered together a group of former royals who fled a menace called The Rapture, eventually ending up on Earth.

description:
Origin

Arlene Dittman is the mother of Terry Dittman, who is married to Bob Stankiewicz. She died of a heart attack due to atherosclerosis. She was revived by an unknown event, as were others in their small rural town Wausau, Wisconsin. Soon she began exhibiting strange behavior, like feeding high blood pressure medication to a zorse (a cross between a zebra and a horse) and pulling out her own teeth, caused they kept growing back. Upon discovery, Arlene attacked and killed her own daughter with pliers. Attacking officer Dana Cypress, Arlene was killed by Martha Cypress with a scythe, severing the top of her skull from the rest of her head.

Laying on the morgue's table, being examined by the doctor, Arlene again came back to life when the doctor put back the top of her skull.
name: Arlene Dittman

teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description:
Origin

Epke Vrooman was a dutch warlock. He was tried in Holland in 1883, but when they put the noose around his neck, he turned into a bundle of sticks and blew away. Discovered living in London, he fled from Edward Grey by ship. On the ship, Vrooman was approached by the seven disciples of Cedu-Barra to choose his body as the next vessel of their master. Before the written spells to resurrect their master were completed, Grey caught up with Vrooman's ship, shot the disciples and drove one of the Lipu daggers into Vrooman's chest. It pierced Cedu-Barra's spirit, trapping him there. Vrooman's inert body was guarded by a young woman who refused to pull the dagger from his body, though he begged her to do it.

Abe Sapien and the B.P.R.D. one day came to the island of Saint-Sébastien to recover the Lipu dagger (not knowing it trapped Cedu-Barra's spirit in Epke Vrooman's body) and dicovered the young woman was now an old woman, still guarding Epke Vrooman's body. Abe Sapien battled the seven disciples. At that moment the dagger fell out of Vrooman's body. The released Vrooman was defeated by the old woman.
name: Epke Vrooman

description:
Origin

Agent Hampton was a B.P.R.D. agent, who died while investigating the alleged corpse of Epke Vrooman several miles from the coast of Saint-Sébastien.
name: Agent Hampton
